                  <tr>
                     <td width="15%" class="TableCell" valign="top"><b>Question:</b><br><a href="http://www.earthdawn-classic.com/faqs/selectTopic.html;jsessionid=a0h_bmGHGcIb?id=203974">Earthdawn Players Compendium FAQ</a><br>
                        	      Last Updated By Dammi on 1/2/06
                     </td>
                     <td width="1%" class="TableCell"><img src="/images/spacer.gif" border="0"></td>
                     <td width="84%" class="TableCell"><b>
                           What Circles are included?
                           </b></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="15%" class="TableCellAlternate" valign="top"><b>Answer:</b></td>
                     <td width="1%" class="TableCellAlternate"><img src="/images/spacer.gif" border="0"></td>
                     <td width="84%" class="TableCellAlternate">
                        The 15 common Disciplines in the Player&rsquo;s Compendium are completely described up to Circle 15. The &rsquo;missing Circles&rsquo;
                        from the minor Disciplines were FASA&rsquo;s way to separate them from the common Disciplines, something which most players
                        with high-Circle characters don&rsquo;t consider as justified (causing many gamemasters to develop the higher Circles on their
                        own). We think that there are other ways to handle this and plan to develop all Disciplines to Circle 15.
                        
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="100%" colspan="3" class="TableCellAlternate">
                        <hr>
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="15%" class="TableCell" valign="top"><b>Question:</b><br><a href="http://www.earthdawn-classic.com/faqs/selectTopic.html;jsessionid=a0h_bmGHGcIb?id=203974">Earthdawn Players Compendium FAQ</a><br>
                        	      Last Updated By Dammi on 1/2/06
                     </td>
                     <td width="1%" class="TableCell"><img src="/images/spacer.gif" border="0"></td>
                     <td width="84%" class="TableCell"><b>
                           Are Race-specific Disciplines (from the Denizens books) included in the Player&rsquo;s Compendium?
                           </b></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="15%" class="TableCellAlternate" valign="top"><b>Answer:</b></td>
                     <td width="1%" class="TableCellAlternate"><img src="/images/spacer.gif" border="0"></td>
                     <td width="84%" class="TableCellAlternate">
                        No, there was not enough space. These Disciplines will appear in Name-giver&rsquo;s Compendium, which is scheduled for 2006.
                        
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="100%" colspan="3" class="TableCellAlternate">
                        <hr>
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="15%" class="TableCell" valign="top"><b>Question:</b><br><a href="http://www.earthdawn-classic.com/faqs/selectTopic.html;jsessionid=a0h_bmGHGcIb?id=203974">Earthdawn Players Compendium FAQ</a><br>
                        	      Last Updated By Dammi on 1/2/06
                     </td>
                     <td width="1%" class="TableCell"><img src="/images/spacer.gif" border="0"></td>
                     <td width="84%" class="TableCell"><b>
                           Do the Racial Modifiers change?
                           </b></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="15%" class="TableCellAlternate" valign="top"><b>Answer:</b></td>
                     <td width="1%" class="TableCellAlternate"><img src="/images/spacer.gif" border="0"></td>
                     <td width="84%" class="TableCellAlternate">
                        Yes - but only for orks. We removed the Dexterity penalty and adjusted their Movement rate.
                        
                     </td>
                  </tr>
